default8.
default              
defaultThe conclusions that the report describes as “(very)
default 
defaulthigh confidence” are unlikely to change significantly in future reports.
default 
defaultThose areas of climate science that are characterised in the report as having lower confidence 
default 
defaultare challenged on a regular basis, and the challenges that stand the test of time are integrated in the following report, reflecting the normal scientific process. Indeed, studies challenging some of the AR5 
defaultWG1 
defaultconclusions are already appearing in the sc
defaultientific literature, often in high impact journals. We are unaware of any barrier that prevents scientists wishing to question the IPCC assessment in the 
defaultpeer-reviewed 
defaultscientific literature
