defaultTo what extent does AR5 reflect the range of views among climate 
defaultscientists?
default9.
default              
defaultThe IPCC review process seems a robust mechanism for ensuring that the range of well-found views (one requirement of which is publication in the scientific literature) is adequately represented. If the IPCC chapter teams should have neglecte
defaultd relevant studies, then the two phases of open review process, the responses to which are overseen by Review Editors, should ensure that significant and relevant studies were represented in subsequent revisions. This is of course reliant on a widespread i
defaultnvolvement in the review process by the community as a whole, but the statistics presented by IPCC indicate a good level of involvement. 
defaultCan any of the areas of the science now be considered settled as a result of AR5’s publication, if so which?
